Khar'Daan is a sunken necropolis deep in the desert, built where warm brackish water rises beneath sandstone.
Its purpose was preserving bodies, identities, contracts, and dynastic legitimacy across generations.
The Covenant of Salt and Flow bound preservation to infrastructure: burial licenses required water contributions, making death a public utility.
Water-debt notation originated in Khar'Daan's burial accounts and later spread across the oasis triad.
The Ninth Meridian Aftershock, triggered by a failed eclipse rite, destabilized the city. Channels burst into the archive quarter.
Noble houses broke seals to retrieve ancestors during the Week of Sundered Measures, spreading contamination.
High priest Sethnekh codified Perpetual Custody: the dead who served in life would serve in death.
This produced oathbound revenant cohorts, annalist wraiths, and sentinel constructs keyed to obsolete warrants.
The Dread Pharaoh is a composite entity assembled from dynastic remains and bound command glyphs.
Its three fused artifacts (Solar Mask, Sealed Tide Cartouche, Night Ledger Core) command constructs and overwrite oathbindings.
Destroying it risks unleashing uncontrolled guardians across every desert route. Perpetual Custody outlived its authors and purpose.
